RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 5F All Weather Track CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOHNNY PAYCHECK steadied after the break when bumped and impeded by PLENTY COUPS, shifted out to the four path when clear, moved up three wide to challenge for the lead near the seven-sixteenths marker, was outside of a three horse battle turning into the stretch, kept to task and got the upper hand in the final yards. JAIME'S COMMITMENT came away well from the gate but was outrun to the turn by PLENTY COUPS, moved up to challenge that one passing the seven-sixteenths pole then raced between horses to the turn, battled gamely down the stretch but was unable to match strides with the winner in the late stages. THECHIEFHASTRICKS was bothered at the break from the action to the immediate outside, made some forward progress racing up the rail to the turn then tried to go through a hole near the three furlong pole that closed, had to take up sharply, lost momentum then re-rallied down the stretch under steady handling to gain third. PLENTY COUPS ducked in after the break and took the path of JOHNNY PAYCHECK, forcing that one to have to take up, sped to a clear early lead, was challenged, then overtaken by a pair to the outside, then battled back to regain the lead at the top of the stretch but gave way passing the furlong marker. SKY EDDIE was off slowly, chased three wide to the stretch then tired in the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 1M All Weather Track CR: 82. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ITS THIEVERY assumed command away from the start, set moderate fractions through the backstretch run while well handled, showed the way into the far turn and was pressed to the quarter pole by DUPLICATION, was set down in upper stretch and held foes at bay to the furlong marker, was confronted by DUPLICATION inside of the furlong marker, battled with that rival into the final sixteenth, drifted out under firm urging in deep stretch and made contact twice with DUPLICATION, dug in in the final strides and gamely lasted for the win at the wire. DUPLICATION was forwardly placed in the early stages and stalked the pace into the first turn, advanced into the backstretch run and attended to the moderate pace while two wide approaching the half-mile marker, pressed ITS THIEVERY to the quarter marker and ran in pursuit of that rival into the stretch, closed on ITS THIEVERY inside of the furlong marker, battled with that rival into deep stretch, was bumped twice by ITS THIEVERY inside of the sixteenth-marker and was denied for the win on the wire, while holding safely for second. PORT O' CALL was allowed to settle in the early running and saved ground into the first turn, saved all of the ground while not far back through the backstretch run, chased heading to the quarter marker, angled three wide into the stretch, rallied outside of the leading pair in the final furlong, could not reel in the top two in deep stretch and was clear at the finish for third. FANTASTIC DREAM stalked the early pace from the inside, saved ground while well positioned through the backstretch run, chased two wide to the quarter marker, was asked for run three wide into the stretch and lacked a late rally. SHERM never far back in the early going, tracked outside of runners into the backstretch run, maintained a three wide path heading into the far turn, chased to the quarter marker, swung four wide into the stretch and gave way. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE RUNNING IN DEEP STRETCH. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT ITS THIEVERY DRIFTED OUT IN THE FINAL SIXTEENTH, MADE CONTACT TWICE WITH DUPLICATION AND COST DUPLICATION THE OPPORTUNITY OF A BETTER PLACING. ITS THIEVERY WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FIRST AND PLACED SECOND. THERE WAS ALSO AN OBJECTION LODGED BY THE RIDER OF DUPLICATION AGAINST THE RIDER OF ITS THIEVERY FOR THE SAME INCIDENT.

ENTRY.OWNER: Ables Frank R Carpenter Chris Jameson Kevin and Peters Mark
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace,well handled,battled deep stretch,dug in,drifted late,held

ENTRY.NAME: Sherm

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 92. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Pr ice $8,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DICK BEST broke alertly and assumed command away from the start, showed the way into the first turn and set a decent pace into the backstretch run, was confronted by CHIEF JACKSON and contested the pace with that rival to the half-mile pole, dueled into the far turn, shook free into upper stretch and was set down approaching the furlong marker, drifted out a bit inside of the furlong marker and lost the lead to IMPLICITLY approaching the sixteenth-pole, battled with that foe into the final stages, gamely came again and was up in the final strides to prevail. IMPLICITLY tracked the decent early pace from the inside, was well placed through the backstretch run while saving ground, chased from the rail heading to the quarter marker, responded to urging and mounted an inside rally in upper stretch, closed well inside of the furlong marker and took a narrow lead nearing the sixteenth-pole, was all out while battling DICK BEST into deep stretch, was bested in the final strides by the winner and held clearly at the finish for second. CHIEF JACKSON was prominent leaving the start and stalked the pace into the first turn, advanced into the backstretch run and contested the pace with DICK BEST heading to the half-mile marker, dueled into the second turn, lost position into upper stretch and chased to the furlong grounds, remained within aim heading into the final sixteenth, was outkicked by the top pair in deep stretch and held for third at the finish. BROKEN FINGER was allowed to settle, saved ground into the backstretch run and advanced heading to the half-mile marker, tracked two wide into the far turn, slipped inside and chased from the rail nearing the top of the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker, lacked the needed response in the late stages and finished evenly. BEL RAGAZZO was unhurried in the early going, maintained an outside path along the first turn and raced thee wide into the backstretch run, was content to tail to the half-mile marker, gained ground into the far turn and chased three wide to the quarter pole, was asked for run four wide into the stretch and did not offer a late response. POUR ON THE COLE stalked the early pace thee wide, gained ground along the backstretch run and tracked two wide into the far turn, lost a bit of ground heading to the quarter marker and chased three wide into the stretch, could not keep pace at the furlong grounds and gave way in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Dick Best
ENTRY.COMMENT: set contested pace,shook free 3/16,lost lead 1/16,came again,game

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 87. Waiver Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOB BOSS broke alertly, was sent to establish the early lead and set a fast pace into the turn, drew to a clear lead heading to the quarter marker while in hand, was kept to task to mid-stretch, extended the lead into the final sixteenth and held clearly for the win at the finish. CHAMPAGNE PEGASUS settled off of the fast early pace and tracked from the inside, advanced while along the rail heading to the quarter marker, angled to the three path into upper stretch, continued to improve position at the furlong grounds, was not able to impact the winner in the late stages but was gaining in deep stretch and ran on to be second best. HOWDOYALIKEMENOW chased the fast pace while outside of an inner rival, raced two wide into the stretch, offered a mild bid at the furlong marker, was outkicked into the final sixteenth and was clear in the end for third. SKY DINSKI lacked early speed, raced three to four wide along the turn and did not threaten in the stretch. EL BERRINCHES was asked for early speed and raced close up to the fast early pace, lost position into the turn and chased MOB BOSS to the quarter marker, saved ground into the stretch and ran evenly to the furlong grounds, lacked a response in the late stages and gave way.

FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Nor thern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs., Unless Entered for the Optional Claiming Price.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALLHERCONTESSA was asked for speed leaving the start and established the front into the first turn, set a decent pace into the backstretch run then rated nicely while showing the way to the half-mile marker, extended the lead into the far turn, was roused at the top of the stretch and drew to a clear lead at the furlong marker, kept to task into the final sixteenth and held for a clear win at the finish. VRONSKY FEINT was away in good order and rated off of the early pace, was shuffled back a bit entering the first turn and raced two wide into the backstretch run, maintained a two wide path through the backstretch run and advanced at the half-mile pole, was steered outside of rivals into the far turn and mounted a four wide rally at the quarter marker, swung three wide into the stretch and chased to the furlong grounds, drifted out a bit at mid-stretch, was not able to impact the winner in the final sixteenth but offered a mild late bid and held safely in the end for second. BELLEO'S FOREST broke alertly and was prominent in the early stages, took back and tracked the pace from the inside along the first turn, advanced into the backstretch run and tracked the moderate pace to the half-mile marker, chased from the inside into the far turn, tipped two wide at the quarter pole and chased CALLHERCONTESSA to mid-stretch, was outkicked in the final sixteenth and held well for third at the finish. BOLD DAUGHTER was a bit fractious in the gate and was away slowly at the start, was unhurried into the first turn and saved ground into the backstretch run, was content to trail to the half-mile marker, was guided to the outside approaching the far turn and gained ground three wide at the quarter pole, swung four wide into the stretch, needed more in the final furlong and was outfinished for third. SKY MAKER settled off of the early pace and tracked from the second flight, maintained a two wide path while between runners through the backstretch run and gained ground at the half-mile marker, came in tight into the far turn and steadied at the five-sixteenths marker, shifted to the rail nearing the top of the stretch and chased to the furlong grounds, could not keep pace into deep stretch and weakened. CAROLE LOMBARD settled inside of runners in the early going, saved ground through the backstretch run and gained ground at the half-mile marker, chased from the inside approaching the quarter pole, lost ground into the stretch, could not muster the needed response in the final stages and finished evenly. SHEZAGHOST was hustled leaving the start and was close up into the first turn, attended to the decent pace into the backstretch run and stalked into the far turn, lost position heading to the quarter marker, was outrun into the stretch, was eased in the final furlong and walked off under her own power. PANDEMIC GIRL was squeezed at the start and was away slowly, was hustled heading into the first turn and tracked the early pace three wide, tracked from the outside through the backstretch run, could not keep pace along the far turn, was eased through the stretch and walked off under her own power.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 1 1/16M Turf CR: 96. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. (One win for $2 5,000 or less will not be considered when determining eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KERRY GOLD showed speed leaving the start and was prominent early on, took back and tracked outside of the leading pair into the first turn, stalked the moderate pace three wide through the backstretch run, was roused into the far turn and mounted a three wide bid at the quarter marker, took command into upper stretch and kicked clear at the furlong grounds, powered home under steady late urging and held for a clear win at the finish. INCREDIBLE SHOT settled off of the early pace and saved ground into the first turn, made a steady advance through the backstretch run and saved all of the ground into the far turn, came in a bit tight nearing the quarter marker and waited for racing room nearing the top of the stretch, tipped three wide into the drive and gained ground at the furlong marker, could not make headway on KERRY GOLD in deep stretch and stayed on to be second best. O B'S was unhurried in the early going, improved position into the backstretch run and tracked the moderate pace three wide to the half-mile pole, continued to move up along the far turn, swung five wide into the stretch and ran evenly to the furlong marker, was outkicked into deep stretch but stayed on in the final stages to secure third. BID ON THE PRIZE was squeezed leaving the start and was away slowly, recovered and tracked the early pace from the second flight, raced outside of rivals along the backstretch run and was well positioned heading to the half-mile marker, advanced into the far turn and mounted a three then four wide bid at the quarter pole, lost ground into the stretch, could not sustain his run into the final furlong, flattened out and was outfinished for third. WILD BILLY D tracked the early pace from the second flight, maintained a two wide path into the backstretch run then slipped to the inside approaching the far turn, made a mild gain at the quarter marker and saved ground into the top of the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker, lacked a response in the final sixteenth and passed tiring rivals in deep stretch. QUALITY CAT was allowed to settle in the early stages, raced two wide into the first turn and maintained that path into the backstretch run, gained ground approaching the half-mile marker and was two wide and between runners heading into the far turn, steadied sharply at the three-furlong pole and negotiated traffic while between and two wide heading to the quarter marker, raced in tight into upper stretch, found running room at the furlong grounds but could not muster a response in the final stages. LIMITED HEATWAVE tracked the early pace from the second flight, maintained a two wide path into the backstretch run and tracked between runners approaching the half-mile pole, navigated traffic into the second turn and chased two wide and between runners to the quarter marker, came four wide into the stretch, was outrun to the furlong grounds and weakened in the final stages. THREEBROTHERS showed speed leaving the start and contested the early pace with TOWN PERFORMER, disputed the moderate pace with that rival through the backstretch run, dueled along the inside into the far turn, was overtaken by KERRY GOLD into the stretch and chased to the furlong grounds, lacked a response in deep stretch and faded in the late stages. TOWN PERFORMER was away in good order and contested the early pace with THREEBROTHERS, disputed the moderate pace through the backstretch run, dueled outside of THREEBROTHERS into the far turn, vied between rivals at the quarter marker, dropped back into upper stretch and tired in the final furlong. CUT ACROSS SHORTY was allowed to settle and saved ground into the first turn, trailed through the backstretch run, swung six wide into the stretch and did not factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Golden Gate H. - Grade3 GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 104. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. By subscription of $50 each to accompany the nomination or by supplementary nomination of $2,000 (which includes all fees) by Friday, October 27. $500 to enter and $500 additional to start with $100,000 Guaranteed. Weig hts, Saturday, October 28. High weights preferred. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Closed Wednesday, October 25, 2023 with 19 nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WAR AT SEA settled just off of the early pace, raced two then three wide through the backstretch run and tracked the moderate pace to the half-mile marker, chased the leaders two wide to the quarter pole, was steered to the four path into upper stretch then shifted six wide approaching the furlong marker, responded to urging and rallied into the final sixteenth, closed fast in deep stretch and was up in the final strides to nail SILENT POET for the win. SILENT POET broke alertly and assumed command away from the start, cleared to the rail into the first turn and set a pressured pace into the backstretch run, was well rated while carving out moderate fractions approaching the half-mile pole, continued to be pressured by I'MGONNABESOMEBODY into the far turn, shook free into the stretch and was set down at the furlong pole, dug in and held foes at bay into the final sixteenth, was all out in the final strides and was nailed on the wire for the win, while besting the rest. TRIPOLI was away in good order, took back off of the early pace and saved ground into the first turn, was well placed while along the rail through the backstretch run, lost a bit of ground while chasing along the far turn, re-rallied into the stretch and vied for the lead at the furlong marker, battled into the final sixteenth, was outkicked in deep stretch and held for third at the finish. LAMMAS (GB) was unhurried in the early running, raced two wide into the backstretch run and made a mild advance at the half-mile pole, was steered outside of runners and loomed four wide approaching the quarter marker, swung five wide into the stretch, battled to the furlong grounds, could not find the needed response in deep stretch and was outfinished. IL BELLATOR tracked the early pace from the outside, maintained that outside path into the backstretch run and was well placed heading to the half-mile marker, mounted a three wide bid along the far turn, swung to the four path into upper stretch and lost position approaching the furlong marker, could not keep pace into deep stretch and weakened. I'MGONNABESOMEBODY was hustled leaving the start and was prominent into the first turn, prompted the moderate pace into the backstretch run and kept close attendance to SILENT POET heading to the half-mile marker, came under pressure while two wide and between runners at the quarter marker, lost position into the stretch and chased to the furlong grounds, lacked a late response and gave way. SUPERMAZEL was allowed to settle in the early stages, saved ground into the backstretch run while not far back, came in a bit tight at the half-mile marker and was shuffled back heading into the far turn, lost contact approaching the quarter pole and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 1M All Weather Track CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SON OF SHANGHAI broke outward at the break, causing a chain reaction of bumps involving UPRIGHT and HOLY SMOKES, quickly recovered and showed good speed, angled towards the rail going into the clubhouse turn but right in front of LAURA'S KIDOUGH forcing that one to take action to avoid clipping heels, pulled the rider quickly to the lead before the six furlong pole, then repelled an early bid from EXCESS ENGLISH with the rider trying to temper the pace, pulled clear when asked to go on near the quarter pole, responded to strong handling down the stretch, drifted out a bit late but held. O'BANION (IRE) sent hard from the break, was successful in gaining the rail and the lead early, backed off the pace when SON OF SHANGHAI and EXCESS ENGLISH quickened in front, saved ground then angled out to the five path for the stretch run, was set down and produced a nice late run but came up short. THE SLAP took up sharply going into the first turn, then steadied again near the just past the thirteen-sixteenths pole, bided time along the rail then started to move forward through the far turn, got a clean run three wide into the stretch, ran on well and was making up ground until having to shift to the inside when SON OF SHANGHAI drifted in front then was out-nodded for second. AMERICAN EMPIRE got the rail position behind the early pacesetters, ran up into the traffic and steadied slightly near the three-quarter pole, dropped back to a mid-pack position down the early part of the backstretch run before making a forward move heading into the far turn, bided time on the inside then tipped out to the two path, had trouble changing leads through the stretch and was out finished. COUNTRY BOY hustled to contest the early pace then backed off through the clubhouse turn, got bounced around a bit between horses near the seven-sixteenths marker, launched a bid through the turn, came into the stretch up the rail and responded when called upon but was not enough. LAURA'S KIDOUGH was very keen going into the first turn, steadied off heels then veered out sharply in a move for self-preservation, but in turn forced UPRIGHT and HOLY SMOKES very wide, pulled the to the front ranks, was hard to place between horses down the backstretch with the rider desperately looking for a way out near the seven-sixteenths pole, found a path near the quarter pole, swung five wide into the stretch and kept to task while never posing a serious threat. EXCESS ENGLISH came away well and raced forwardly through the first turn, entered the backstretch run contesting the early pace with SON OF SHANGHAI but backed off a bit, content to stalk that one through the far turn, got in tight quarters at the top of the stretch, steadied off heels and could not recover. WOLF'S LIFE was last away from the gate and slow into stride, fell far behind early, chased the field without making up much ground despite being under a drive for the last half mile, did manage to pass a couple of stragglers before the finish. UPRIGHT took a bump from SON OF SHANGHAI after the break then in turn bumped into HOLY SMOKES, then got sandwiched between those two a few strides later, got going then took another bump from LAURA'S KIDOUGH entering the first the first turn then got carried wide when that rival shifted out sharply, avoided any further incidents while racing four to five wide down the backstretch and through the turn but had nothing to offer in the stretch and was not persevered with late. HOLY SMOKES got carried very wide into the first turn, was content to race four to five wide down the backstretch and near the rear of the pack, moved in a couple of paths for the run through the turn, came under pressure near the five-sixteenths marker but did not respond.
